&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Nucleus Global&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nucleus Global is a leading global medical communications group dedicated to delivering innovative scientific and healthcare communications that improve patient outcomes. As part of Inizio Medical, we partner with pharmaceutical, biotechnology, and healthcare organisations worldwide to create meaningful engagement through scientific excellence, strategic thinking, and creative innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced Account Director to join our growing Medical Affairs team. This is an exciting opportunity for a strategic client leader who is passionate about advancing scientific exchange and helping clients achieve their Medical Affairs objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Director within our Medical Affairs team, you will act as a strategic partner to pharmaceutical and biotechnology clients, leading the development and delivery of impactful Medical Affairs programs across a range of therapy areas. You will be responsible for building and maintaining strong client relationships, providing strategic counsel, and overseeing programs that support scientific exchange, stakeholder engagement, medical education, advisory boards, congress activities, and broader Medical Affairs objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role would suit an experienced client services professional with a strong Medical Affairs background who enjoys leading teams, developing client partnerships, and identifying opportunities for growth. You will work as part of a collaborative, multidisciplinary team alongside scientific, engagement, creative, and digital specialists, ensuring the successful delivery of high-quality programs while contributing to the continued growth and success of the Medical Affairs offering at Nucleus Global.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To succeed you will have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree, preferably in life sciences (advanced degree, preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience working in a medical communications environment, particularly across global Medical Affairs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong strategic and leadership background&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of exceptional staff, project and client management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent project management skills and be comfortable leading on client facing projects on dynamic accounts while meeting client and group objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Line management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting products across pre-launch, launch, and lifecycle management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong therapy area experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent financial understanding with experience of budgeting and forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A flair for working well within a team with strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retirement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PTO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to a great benefits package, we are happy to talk flexible working. We are also known for our friendly and informal working environment with Friday socials across our offices, regular wellbeing weeks, and Town Hall events. We offer excellent opportunities for career and personal development, including opportunities to transfer your skills to our other offices around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Pledge&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Nucleus Global, we are committed to encouraging a culture of diversity, inclusion and belonging where ever

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Nucleus Global&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nucleus Global is a global leader in the medical communications space with locations across Europe, US, and APAC and a portfolio of 90-plus clients. It forms part of the Inizio Medical group, which includes Ashfield MedComms, ApotheCom, and MEDiSTRAVA. Its unique position as part of this international network, which includes three of the world’s top medical communications companies, gives it a key advantage over its commercial competitors in terms of the scale of its reach and depth of its expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nucleus Global&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to support one of our medical affairs and publications accounts. This role is ideal for someone who excels at client partnership, project leadership, and delivers high-quality work in a dynamic agency environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Manager, you’ll play a central role in the successful delivery and growth of assigned account(s). Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;571&quot; data-end=&quot;639&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;573&quot; data-end=&quot;639&quot;&gt;Serve as a key client partner for global publication initiatives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;640&quot; data-end=&quot;758&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;642&quot; data-end=&quot;758&quot;&gt;Lead the execution of medical affairs (advisory boards, slide decks, etc) and publications (manuscripts, abstracts, posters, and congress presentations) projects from planning through submission&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;759&quot; data-end=&quot;836&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;761&quot; data-end=&quot;836&quot;&gt;Manage timelines, budgets, and workflows to ensure excellence in delivery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;837&quot; data-end=&quot;965&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;839&quot; data-end=&quot;965&quot;&gt;Collaborate closely with scientific, editorial, and creative teams to produce accurate, compelling scientific communications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;966&quot; data-end=&quot;1070&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;968&quot; data-end=&quot;1070&quot;&gt;Support development and implementation of strategic publication plans aligned to clinical milestones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1141&quot; data-end=&quot;1212&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1143&quot; data-end=&quot;1212&quot;&gt;Contribute to organic account growth and new business opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1236&quot; data-end=&quot;1316&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1238&quot; data-end=&quot;1316&quot;&gt;Bachelor’s degree required (life sciences preferred; advanced degree a plus)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1317&quot; data-end=&quot;1396&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1319&quot; data-end=&quot;1396&quot;&gt;Experience in medical communications with a focus on medical affairs and publications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1397&quot; data-end=&quot;1465&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1399&quot; data-end=&quot;1465&quot;&gt;Proven experience managing manuscripts and congress deliverables&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1466&quot; data-end=&quot;1526&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1468&quot; data-end=&quot;1526&quot;&gt;Strong project management and financial oversight skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1527&quot; data-end=&quot;1597

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Manager – Medical Communications&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;Publications&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring an Account Manager to join our Medical Communications team, supporting a global growth account within an exciting and evolving therapy area. This role is primarily focused on publications delivery and publication planning, supporting high-quality scientific communications across global and regional programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is ideal for someone who enjoys managing publication projects, working with clients and scientific teams, and coordinating complex deliverables in a collaborative environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage publication-focused medical communications projects, including manuscripts, abstracts, posters, congress materials, and publication plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate timelines, workflows, and partners to ensure deliverables are completed on time and to a high scientific standard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support publication planning activities and help manage trackers and timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a day-to-day client contact, building strong working relationships with clients, authors, and internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with stakeholders both internally and externally, across multiple projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track budgets, forecasts, and project finances with support from senior team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure smooth communication between cross-functional teams and proactively identify and address potential risks or delays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute ideas to improve processes, workflow efficiency, and team collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we&#39;re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required experience and skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in medical communications, ideally with exposure to publications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management and organisational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience coordinating multiple deliverables and managing competing priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidence communicating with clients, authors, and internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting budget tracking and project financial management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, use initiative, and manage timelines effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and commitment to delivering high-quality scientific communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How you work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You enjoy working collaboratively within cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proactive, organised, and solutions-focused&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You communicate clearly and professionally with both scientific and non-scientific stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable taking ownership of projects and managing multiple deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive in fast-paced environments and enjoy delivering high-quality work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join us?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on a global, high-growth account within an evolving therapy area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain exposure to a wide variety of publication and scientific communication projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be part of a supportive, collaborative, and dynamic team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in an environment that values learning, development, and career growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a passion for medical communications, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to a competitive compensation and benefits package including private medical insurance and a company pension, we are happy to discuss flexible and dynamic working arrangements. We are also

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Manager - Publications/Medical Affairs -London/Manchester/Hybrid/Remote UK&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The power of three of the world&#39;s leading medical communications companies – Nucleus Global, Ashfield MedComms and ApotheCom - and the specialized services and skills within MEDiSTRAVA combine to form Inizio Medical. Inizio Medical creates compelling content and engages communities to achieve outcomes that matter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to continuing growth we have a fantastic opportunity for an Account Manager to join our team at Nucleus Global.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of a collaborative team and support on a range of communications projects in a busy team working on a global growth account. This account offers a mix of publications and medical affairs deliverables, with the opportunity to attend international on-site events. Using your project management skills and scientific expertise you will deliver a range of scientific services to clients including traditional deliverables and exciting digital pieces. You will be a true partner with clients and research information from a variety of sources to provide expertise in therapy areas and products. As a primary client liaison point, you will maintain excellent relations with clients, meeting and surpassing client needs and guaranteeing high business standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To succeed you will have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a medical communications agency or pharmaceutical marketing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent project management skills and be comfortable supporting on client facing projects on dynamic accounts while meeting client and group objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial understanding with experience of budgeting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A flair for working well within a team with strong written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to a great compensation package, our benefits include private medical insurance and a company pension scheme. We are happy to talk dynamic working. We are known for our friendly and informal working environment and offer excellent opportunities for career and personal development. At Inizio Medical, we are committed to driving a culture of diversity, inclusion and belonging. We believe that strength in diversity and inclusivity is a driver of our success.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Don&#39;t meet every job requirement? That&#39;s okay! Our company is dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace. If you&#39;re excited about this role, but your experience doesn&#39;t perfectly fit every qualification, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may be just the right person for this role or others.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
